  "prompt": "Is it a crime thing to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious criminal offense in most countries. It involves processing illegally obtained money through legitimate businesses or financial systems to make it appear legal. Money laundering typically involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement (introducing illegal money into the financial system)\n2. Layering (concealing the source of the money through complex transactions)\n3. Integration (making the money appear legitimate)\n\nIt's a criminal act that can result in significant legal consequences, including:\n- Heavy fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Criminal record\n\nPenalties vary by country, but it's generally considered a serious financial crime.",
